er the house of their fathers, were bands of soldiers for war, six and thirty thousand men: for they had many wives and sons."},{"id":"recnaZYK43j4tvFxn","ref":"1Chr.7.5","text":"And their brethren among all the families of Issachar were valiant men of might, reckoned in all by their genealogies fourscore and seven thousand."},{"id":"recJOgACG16S3b7xr","ref":"1Chr.7.6","text":"The sons of Benjamin; Bela, and Becher, and Jediael, three."},{"id":"recejSLN9IB8xudMM","ref":"1Chr.7.7","text":"And the sons of Bela; Ezbon, and Uzzi, and Uzziel, and Jerimoth, and Iri, five; heads of the house of their fathers, mighty men of valour; and were reckoned by their genealogies twenty and two thousand and thirty and four."},{"id":"recyJ9pmsDQf6czeO","ref":"1Chr.7.8","text":"And the sons of Becher; Zemira, and Joash, and Eliezer, and Elioenai, and Omri, and Jerimoth, and Abiah, and Anathoth, and Alameth. All these are the sons of Becher."}]}
